The SANDF and South African Airways put on a spectacular display at the inauguration of President Cyril Ramaphosa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Defence Force and South African Airways put on a spectacular display atÂ President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration. At a ceremony fit for royalty Ramaphosa asserted himself as the commander in chief. After being sworn in, he and the crowd at Loftus Stadium watched a military parade. READ: Ramaphosa promises jobs and justice Meanwhile, a parachutist crash-landed during the inauguration. A number of parachutists landed on the rugby field but one crashed into a pole. The person remained on the field for some time afterward and it's still unclear what his or her condition is.